# Architecture Overview

This project is a classical ML pipeline for fake news detection and claim-level truthfulness
classification using TF-IDF features and linear models.

## High-level flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A[Raw Data\nFake/True CSVs\nLIAR TSVs] --> B[Preprocessing\nText cleaning + schema normalization]
  B --> C[Feature Extraction\nMulti-view TF-IDF]
  C --> D[Models\nLogReg / Linear SVM\nOptional calibration]
  D --> E[Evaluation\nMetrics + plots]
  E --> F[Artifacts\nJSON/CSV/PNGs]
```

## Core modules

- `src/preprocessing.py`: dataset loading, label mapping, text cleaning
- `src/features.py`: TF-IDF feature builder and LIAR-specific view selection
- `src/models.py`: model training and tuning
- `src/evaluation.py`: metrics and curve utilities
- `experiments/`: runnable scripts that orchestrate the pipeline
